  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technical Superintendent",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>To manage the daily operation of the number of vessels assigned to him in accordance with ASL’s HSSEQ</li>\n  <li>System.</li>\n  <li>Plan, manage, monitor and execute vessels repairs, dry dockings and conversions within agreed budgets.</li>\n  <li>Monitor the vessels performance trend and take necessary remedial actions to optimize vessel’s operations.·</li>\n  <li>Collection, Evaluation of Emission control / compliance data from ships and approval from relevant authorities (SEEMP / EEXI / CII).</li>\n  <li>Follow up class and statutory certification status, condition of class and arrange for the necessary surveys (flag state, certification for Panama Canal etc.)</li>\n  <li>Visit vessels regularly (at least two times a year, in Port + Sailing), prepare visit reports and follow up with</li>\n  <li>closure of deficiencies observed·</li>\n  <li>Prepare biannual, triannual or quarterly management reports, as agreed with each Principal, for the General</li>\n  <li>Manager’s approval.</li>\n  <li>Maintain strict cost control of the Annual Operating Budget for each of the assigned vessels.</li>\n  <li>Review monthly cost control and approve monthly financial reports before sending to Technical Manager for</li>\n  <li>review.</li>\n  <li>Actively participate in training and education of new crew and Office Staff joining ASL.</li>\n  <li>Assists SIRE inspection, TMSA audits</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Requirements:</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n  <li>Marine Engineer Class 1 ( Chief Engineer Unlimited ) Certificate. Minimum 5 Years of Tanker experience is</li>\n  <li>mandatory.</li>\n  <li>Possess relevant sea-going work experience as Chief Engineer with minimum class 1 certification within</li>\n  <li>experience in LPG / Oil tanker for a minimum 2 years.</li>\n  <li>Experience working as a Technical Superintendent, and preferably with tankers (LPG / Oil) would be an</li>\n  <li>advantage.</li>\n  <li>Hard-working and strong team player</li>\n  <li>Possess good organizational and communication skills and hands-on.</li>\n  <li>Ability to travel within short notice as required</li>\n</ul>",
